<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/476184-i-love-dark-retellings-but-the-ones-i">I love dark retellings, but the ones I read usually tend to be YA. Just how dark is this one?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_476184'><a id="like_count_community_question_476184" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/476184?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F6308379-the-child-thief">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/476184-i-love-dark-retellings-but-the-ones-i">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/476184-i-love-dark-retellings-but-the-ones-i">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7375157-karen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1641413856i/7375157._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7375157-karen">Karen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Not as dark as I anticipated. I was hesitant to read it, but I love Peter Pan and Arthurian legend, so I went for it. Don&apos;t get me wrong, there was de<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Not as dark as I anticipated. I was hesitant to read it, but I love Peter Pan and Arthurian legend, so I went for it. Don't get me wrong, there was definitely some explicit gore and major moral ambiguity, and I certainly wouldn't let my 11 year old read it. Having said that, I thought it was fantastic and thought provoking. Not as gruesome or dark as say, George RR Martin's stuff. Plus, the illustrations are phenomenal and just add to the story. Definitely check those out prior to/while you're reading.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
