  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1500167141" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1500167141" />
    <a title="Cara " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47381612-cara"><img alt="Cara " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493198128p2/47381612.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1500167141?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cara " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cara " href="/user/show/47381612-cara">Cara </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1500167141" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5207069674099593850">4.75 ⭐️<br/><br/>&quot;Don&apos;t let them steal your magic&quot; <br/><br/>Oh wow. Oh wow. THIS WAS AMAZING. The Child Thief is a retelling of Peter Pan but a lot darker and I am here for it. I heard about this book about 2 years ago and like literally EVERY BOOK EVER I put off reading it for no reason whatsoever and I so regret that. <br/><br/>Peter is a &quot;child&quot; (he&apos;s really like thousands of years old but he doesn&apos;t age and such remember) who travels to the real world and lures children who have had a rough life or are going through a h</span>
  <span id="freeText5207069674099593850" style="display:none">4.75 ⭐️<br /><br />"Don't let them steal your magic" <br /><br />Oh wow. Oh wow. THIS WAS AMAZING. The Child Thief is a retelling of Peter Pan but a lot darker and I am here for it. I heard about this book about 2 years ago and like literally EVERY BOOK EVER I put off reading it for no reason whatsoever and I so regret that. <br /><br />Peter is a "child" (he's really like thousands of years old but he doesn't age and such remember) who travels to the real world and lures children who have had a rough life or are going through a hard time into 'the mist' which leads to Avalon a world once filled with Magic and beauty but is now slowing dying. Peter recruits these kids into his little gang and essentially expect them to give up their lives fighting for him and his cause to save Avalon, which they do mind you. Nick has recently fallen into bad company and is looking for a way out when Peter finds him and that's where the book starts. <br /><br />This is one of those rare books I find where it was completely balanced and the plot wasn't relying on the characters or vice versa everything molded and weaved together seamlessly, the plot, the characters and the writing were all on par with one another. <br /><br />Each character in the story was well thought out and complex each of their stories playing into one another and building very real characters. All of the characters in the book were neither good nor bad but morally gray and you could see why each person would do what they're doing and see where they're coming from. I saw in other reviews of this book people had a problem with Peter and him not learning a lesson throughout the book and essentially not growing up but I think that's the point Peter is supposed to be a kid forever and what do kids do? Well they make mistakes, they damage things, they cause problems with really almost no thought to the repercussions of those actions and how they'll play out later. Kids also move on from things really fast, something bad could happen and in a matter of minutes they would've moved past it so Peters character really isn't surprising and I like the fact that he's consistent throughout the novel and doesn't have a huge out of character change. Also don't get me wrong this isn't me saying all kids are assholes and don't care about anyone but themselves but just generally kids care less about stuff than adults or teenagers would. <br /><br />Also this is a personal thing but the fact that there was zero romance in this was a HUGE plus for me throughout the book. <br /><br />All through the novel the whole story was made darker when you remembered that these were kids and that they've been through so much and have done so much that no one should have to go through and do let alone kids.<br /><br />But yeah this book Issa love and you should definitely read it </span>
  <a data-text-id="5207069674099593850" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


